This week, we enter a new month and Mercury enters Pisces. It sparks a surge of creativity, renewal, fresh thinking, illuminating conversations and innovative ideas comes to us naturally and easily – like a tap turned on. Feel the flow and encourage your imagination to keep on delivering the goods. With this free flow of great ideas and hopeful ambitions, it’s a time to reset your best hopes and resolutions. What good intentions can you bring to the month ahead? How can you start as you mean to go on in March? Let the tarot guide you. March 21 to April 20 Tarot card for Aries for this week: Knight of Swords Meaning: Be bold, be forthright, be a bit selfish, dare I say. We are heading into your astrological season when your powers are at their fiercest. Get ready to make headway and go for your heart’s desires. The Knight of Swords is riding beside you, protecting you, urging you on, fighting battles with and for you. This is a season where you need to push your own agenda and your own desires. Follow passion. Pursue ambition. Be your best self and get the rewards. Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aries April 21 to May 21 Tarot card for Taurus for this week: Three of Coins Meaning: To get ahead you need the backing and input of other people sometimes, and this is one of those times. The Three of Coins shows that people value you. They see how you behave and the efforts you make and the way you conduct yourself, and they like what they see! So, now you need to manifest something from this goodwill, from this surge of appreciation. Be visible, showcase your talents, make demands, ask for help, get their ear. You’ll be surprised how far you can go. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Taurus May 22 to June 21 Tarot card for Gemini for this week: Eight of Coins Meaning: You need to dig in and persevere Gemini. I know you’re tired of certain things, tasks, or even people. I know you are itching to dance away and join a new party…