ons. You deserve everything coming to you. You deserve the rewards. Make sure you get them. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Virgo September 24 to October 23 Tarot card for Libra for this week: Eight of Swords Meaning: This is all about deconstruction, in a positive way. Identifying and dismantling self-limiting beliefs and behaviours which have gotten in your way in the past. We are all our own worst enemy. Waking up to this fact and dealing with it can be life changing. When you’re an ally to yourself, you have the person who knows you best on side. This makes you unstoppable, authentic, in tune with what you need and want. Face your demons. Banish the inner critic Head here for everything you need to know about being a Libra October 24 to November 22 Tarot card for Scorpio for this week: Ten of Swords Meaning: The Ten of Swords pulls no punches. It’s a demand. It’s harsh. And it’s here to tell you that there are some things in your life which must come to an end. You know what they are because they cause you pain, stress, and sleepless nights, and have done for a while (and they aren’t going to improve either). Enough is enough, Scorpio. Protect yourself and your peace of mind and withdraw from any and all toxicity around you. Leave them to it. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Scorpio November 23 to December 21 Tarot card for Sagittarius for this week: Two of Coins Meaning: The Two of Coins is a great card for you, Sagittarius. Abundance, variety, can-do attitude, fulfilment. The more you do, the more you can do. You are ruled by Jupiter and this energy is reflected in this card. You are going to be super busy, offered lots of opportunities, and you’re ready to walk into the sunshine with your head high. Be positive, be happy, be ready for anything. Importantly, say yes often! Head here for everything you need to know about being a Sagittarius December 22 to January 21 Tarot card for Capricorn for this week: Page of Swords Meaning: Don’t hedge your bets this week or blow hot and cold on people. Set a decisive tone for March. Be forthright and direct. The Page of Swords is giving you the green light to progress on the things you’re keen to do. It may mean saying no to a few other things because you must prioritise vs try and capture every gem. People need answers. People want clarity. Give it to them and watch the momentum pick up as their support then grows. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Capricorn January 22 to February 19 Tarot card for Aquarius for this week: Page of Wands Meaning: Start the month with a week of new news. Bring in as many new ideas, activities, people, and trials as is humanly possible this week and March will be exciting, educational, and full of learning. The Page of Wands has a go, he tries new stuff, no pressure or expectation, just an open mind. This is your kind of attitude too. You just need to push the new content a bitand make it happen. Get the momentum going this week and things will flow your way all month long. Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aquarius February 20 to March 20 Tarot card for Pisces for this week: Five of Swords Meaning: Start the month by seeking peace, a truce, a respite, an ending to any and all stressful or difficult situations in your life. Find peace of mind. The Five of Swords is a reminder that arguing is just noise, no one wins, things usually get worse. You are a natural peace-seeker but you’ve been drawn into some conflict. Find a way out, even if it is just a temporary truce (though you can bet that, once the noise ends, so will the drama). Make March a relaxing month. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Pisces Your daily Metro.co.uk horoscope is here every morning, seven days a week (yes, including weekends!). To check your forecast, head to our dedicated horoscopes page. Kerry King, the tarot queen, uses tarot and star sign wisdom to create inspiring